cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.DM, cs.MM, cs.CC 

This paper deals with the design and construction of codes for multimedia fingerprinting schemes, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses combinatorial properties of the codes, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper mentions multimedia applications, which could be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CC).
